### Hadith 1:639

*Narrated Anas bin Sirin:*

I heard Anas saying, "A man from Ansar said to the Prophet, 'I cannot
pray with you (in congregation).' He was a very fat man and he prepared
a meal for the Prophet and invited him to his house. He spread out a mat
for the Prophet, and washed one of its sides with water, and the Prophet
prayed two Rakat on it." A man from the family of Al-Jaruid asked, "Did
the Prophet used to pray the Duha (forenoon) prayer?" Anas said, "I did
not see him praying the Duha prayer except on that day."

